laboratory_examinations.findings: Subsegmental atelectasis at the lung bases; liver shows homogenous attenuation with a 5.1 cm area of enhancement; pancreas normal; spleen normal; normal kidneys with a subcentimeter hypodensity in the left kidney likely representing a cyst; right lower quadrant likely reflecting a dilated appendix with associated periappendiceal fat stranding and a suggested 4 mm fecalith; no evidence of crucial abnormalities.
